probably, the biggest guarantee

00:08:36.056 --> 00:08:37.126 A:middle
that you'll get is that these

00:08:37.126 --> 00:08:38.126 A:middle
translation lengths are going to

00:08:38.126 --> 00:08:38.635 A:middle
be different.

00:08:39.145 --> 00:08:40.226 A:middle
They're going to be much shorter

00:08:40.226 --> 00:08:41.525 A:middle
or much longer, depending on the

00:08:41.525 --> 00:08:42.086 A:middle
language.

00:08:42.385 --> 00:08:44.236 A:middle
And this is something that your

00:08:44.236 --> 00:08:45.546 A:middle
design and layout should adapt

00:08:45.546 --> 00:08:45.866 A:middle
for.

00:08:48.136 --> 00:08:49.466 A:middle
On top of this, there's also

00:08:49.466 --> 00:08:50.846 A:middle
directionality, like I mentioned

00:08:50.846 --> 00:08:51.286 A:middle
before.

00:08:52.036 --> 00:08:53.306 A:middle
Because some languages are

00:08:53.306 --> 00:08:54.876 A:middle
written in right to left this

00:08:54.876 --> 00:08:56.656 A:middle
has some design considerations,

00:08:56.996 --> 00:08:58.106 A:middle
not just in the text that you

00:08:58.106 --> 00:08:59.866 A:middle
have in your app, but also, the

00:08:59.866 --> 00:09:01.146 A:middle
way you present information.

00:08:59.866 --> 00:09:01.146 A:middle
way you present information.

00:09:01.446 --> 00:09:03.026 A:middle
Especially, horizontally flowing

00:09:03.026 --> 00:09:05.136 A:middle
information and how that general

00:09:05.136 --> 00:09:06.846 A:middle
flow should adapt for both

00:09:06.846 --> 00:09:10.966 A:middle
script and writing directions.

00:09:12.186 --> 00:09:13.236 A:middle
So, a great starting point to

00:09:13.236 --> 00:09:14.716 A:middle
help you do all of this is Auto

00:09:14.716 --> 00:09:15.066 A:middle
Layout.

00:09:15.236 --> 00:09:16.226 A:middle
You might have heard of Auto

00:09:16.226 --> 00:09:16.916 A:middle
Layout, before.

00:09:17.686 --> 00:09:19.116 A:middle
This is a powerful technology

00:09:19.116 --> 00:09:20.266 A:middle
that is at the core of our

00:09:20.266 --> 00:09:20.966 A:middle
layout engine.

00:09:21.736 --> 00:09:23.006 A:middle
And Auto Layout, instead of

00:09:23.006 --> 00:09:26.026 A:middle
describing explicit frames or

00:09:26.116 --> 00:09:27.606 A:middle
positions of your controls and

00:09:27.606 --> 00:09:30.286 A:middle
labels, describes constraints or

00:09:30.286 --> 00:09:31.586 A:middle
relationships between these

00:09:31.586 --> 00:09:32.016 A:middle
views.

00:09:32.356 --> 00:09:33.666 A:middle
And therefore, how they're

00:09:33.666 --> 00:09:34.876 A:middle
positioned relative to each

00:09:34.876 --> 00:09:36.216 A:middle
other and how they're allowed to

00:09:36.316 --> 00:09:37.866 A:middle
grow relative to each other.

00:09:40.206 --> 00:09:41.686 A:middle
On top of this constraint-based

00:09:41.686 --> 00:09:43.466 A:middle
system we have the idea of

00:09:43.546 --> 00:09:44.356 A:middle
leading and trailing

00:09:44.356 --> 00:09:45.036 A:middle
constraints.

00:09:45.916 --> 00:09:46.976 A:middle
And what this means is that

00:09:47.346 --> 00:09:48.466 A:middle
this, essentially, describes

00:09:48.506 --> 00:09:50.166 A:middle
properties that are left and

00:09:50.166 --> 00:09:51.896 A:middle
