00:32:59.486 --> 00:33:02.096 A:middle
What do I mean by a style?

00:32:59.486 --> 00:33:02.096 A:middle
What do I mean by a style?

00:33:02.666 --> 00:33:04.496 A:middle
So, broadly speaking, I'm

00:33:04.496 --> 00:33:06.316 A:middle
referring to aspects of your

00:33:06.316 --> 00:33:07.616 A:middle
text that you choose once you've

00:33:07.616 --> 00:33:08.666 A:middle
chosen a typeface.

00:33:09.176 --> 00:33:11.276 A:middle
So, let's say the font weight,

00:33:11.746 --> 00:33:13.616 A:middle
like how bold it is, or whether

00:33:13.616 --> 00:33:16.036 A:middle
it's italicized, and what the

00:33:16.086 --> 00:33:17.246 A:middle
size of the font may be.

00:33:19.546 --> 00:33:21.636 A:middle
So, the key thing to keep in

00:33:21.636 --> 00:33:23.246 A:middle
mind is that some aspects

00:33:23.816 --> 00:33:26.156 A:middle
translate better to other

00:33:26.156 --> 00:33:27.286 A:middle
languages and others don't.

00:33:27.286 --> 00:33:29.086 A:middle
So, let's take a look at an

00:33:29.086 --> 00:33:31.436 A:middle
example of where something might

00:33:31.466 --> 00:33:32.136 A:middle
not translate.

00:33:32.876 --> 00:33:34.306 A:middle
So, here we have a simple string

00:33:34.306 --> 00:33:34.816 A:middle
in English.

00:33:35.586 --> 00:33:36.866 A:middle
We've italicized Mars and 2

00:33:36.866 --> 00:33:37.946 A:middle
Travelers to indicate that

00:33:37.946 --> 00:33:39.266 A:middle
they're variables, so they can

00:33:39.266 --> 00:33:39.646 A:middle
change.

00:33:41.666 --> 00:33:42.936 A:middle
And this is how it translates

00:33:42.936 --> 00:33:43.966 A:middle
into traditional Chinese.

00:33:45.496 --> 00:33:46.376 A:middle
There are a couple of issues

00:33:46.916 --> 00:33:47.000 A:middle
here.

00:33:48.936 --> 00:33:51.426 A:middle
Mars is italicized in English.

00:33:51.586 --> 00:33:54.126 A:middle
It's not italicized in Chinese.

00:33:54.336 --> 00:33:54.696 A:middle
Why?

00:33:55.096 --> 00:33:56.716 A:middle
Because italicization is not a

00:33:56.716 --> 00:33:57.726 A:middle
concept in Chinese.

00:33:57.856 --> 00:33:58.926 A:middle
And it's not a concept in,

00:33:58.926 --> 00:34:00.596 A:middle
actually, most scripts outside

00:33:58.926 --> 00:34:00.596 A:middle
actually, most scripts outside

00:34:00.596 --> 00:34:01.696 A:middle
of Latin, Cyrillic, and Greek.

00:34:03.406 --> 00:34:04.936 A:middle
So, a design that uses italics,

00:34:05.366 --> 00:34:06.186 A:middle
probably, won't work.

00:34:06.996 --> 00:34:08.886 A:middle
The other thing to note is that

00:34:08.886 --> 00:34:10.076 A:middle
in Chinese there are no spaces

00:34:10.076 --> 00:34:11.326 A:middle
between words, and also, there

00:34:11.326 --> 00:34:13.206 A:middle
is no concept of uppercase and

00:34:13.206 --> 00:34:13.936 A:middle
lowercase letters.

00:34:14.306 --> 00:34:15.626 A:middle
So, you kind of lose a natural

00:34:15.626 --> 00:34:17.085 A:middle
distinction that you get in

00:34:17.085 --> 00:34:18.485 A:middle
English when you translate it

00:34:19.326 --> 00:34:19.976 A:middle
into Chinese.

00:34:20.286 --> 00:34:21.985 A:middle
A couple of small things to

00:34:21.985 --> 00:34:23.255 A:middle
note, also, is that the word

00:34:23.255 --> 00:34:25.775 A:middle
order is different.

00:34:25.896 --> 00:34:27.406 A:middle
And also, because the 2 still

00:34:27.406 --> 00:34:29.106 A:middle
comes from the Latin script and

00:34:29.106 --> 00:34:30.646 A:middle
is still italicized, it doesn't

00:34:30.646 --> 00:34:31.806 A:middle
look great.

00:34:32.755 --> 00:34:34.315 A:middle
So, how can you fix this?

00:34:35.846 --> 00:34:38.346 A:middle
Well, the keys to realizing that

00:34:38.346 --> 00:34:39.755 A:middle
you're doing emphasis, not

00:34:39.755 --> 00:34:41.106 A:middle
necessarily italics.

00:34:41.656 --> 00:34:42.886 A:middle
And emphasis can be done in

00:34:42.886 --> 00:34:43.835 A:middle
multiple different ways.

00:34:44.045 --> 00:34:44.956 A:middle
This is a great way to do

00:34:44.956 --> 00:34:46.096 A:middle
emphasis that works across

00:34:46.186 --> 00:34:47.186 A:middle
several different languages.

00:34:47.295 --> 00:34:48.386 A:middle
In fact, it works for all the

00:34:48.386 --> 00:34:49.926 A:middle
languages that we support, which

00:34:49.926 --> 00:34:52.636 A:middle
is to bold a given word.

00:34:53.166 --> 00:34:57.256 A:middle
Lastly, let's talk about

00:34:57.366 --> 00:34:58.866 A:middle
emphasis at a character level or

00:34:58.866 --> 00:34:59.916 A:middle
sub-word level.

00:35:01.476 --> 00:35:02.596 A:middle
Let's say we have an app with a

00:35:02.656 --> 00:35:04.696 A:middle
Search feature and we want to

00:35:04.696 --> 00:35:05.866 A:middle
highlight the part of the

00:35:05.866 --> 00:35:07.326 A:middle
results that matched to make it

00:35:07.326 --> 00:35:08.266 A:middle
clear to the user what's

00:35:08.266 --> 00:35:08.706 A:middle
happening.

00:35:09.636 --> 00:35:11.066 A:middle
Now, this works really well for

00:35:11.066 --> 00:35:13.756 A:middle
English, by using a bolder

00:35:13.756 --> 00:35:14.986 A:middle
weight for the matched segment.

00:35:15.676 --> 00:35:19.716 A:middle
It works really badly for Hindi.

00:35:20.226 --> 00:35:23.446 A:middle
So, what you're seeing here, so

00:35:23.476 --> 00:35:24.916 A:middle
anybody who can read Hindi will

00:35:24.916 --> 00:35:26.056 A:middle
tell you that everything on the

00:35:26.056 --> 00:35:27.176 A:middle
right-hand side looks completely

00:35:27.176 --> 00:35:27.596 A:middle
broken.

00:35:28.406 --> 00:35:31.096 A:middle
Any time you see a dotted circle

00:35:31.346 --> 00:35:33.646 A:middle
inside a Hindi word, something

00:35:33.646 --> 00:35:34.926 A:middle
has gone very, very wrong.

00:35:35.896 --> 00:35:37.396 A:middle
And the reason this is happening

00:35:37.796 --> 00:35:39.286 A:middle
is because even though it's the

00:35:39.286 --> 00:35:40.826 A:middle
same font family, different

00:35:40.826 --> 00:35:42.716 A:middle
weights within that font are,

00:35:42.716 --> 00:35:43.926 A:middle
actually, a different font.

00:35:44.326 --> 00:35:45.446 A:middle
And you can't have the

00:35:45.446 --> 00:35:46.996 A:middle
appropriate joining behavior for

00:35:46.996 --> 00:35:48.956 A:middle
languages like Hindi if you have

00:35:48.996 --> 00:35:49.836 A:middle
two different fonts.

00:35:51.466 --> 00:35:54.026 A:middle
So, one easy way to solve this

00:35:54.026 --> 00:35:55.856 A:middle
problem is use a different kind

00:35:55.856 --> 00:35:57.316 A:middle
of emphasis at a character

00:35:57.316 --> 00:35:57.526 A:middle
level.

00:35:57.526 --> 00:35:58.596 A:middle
So, at a character level you can

00:35:58.596 --> 00:36:00.766 A:middle
use something like using a

00:35:58.596 --> 00:36:00.766 A:middle
use something like using a

00:36:02.016 --> 00:36:02.666 A:middle
different color.

00:36:03.286 --> 00:36:04.966 A:middle
For example, here we use black

00:36:04.966 --> 00:36:07.146 A:middle
color for the math segment and

00:36:07.226 --> 00:36:08.206 A:middle
gray for the remainder of the

00:36:08.206 --> 00:36:08.486 A:middle
word.

00:36:08.936 --> 00:36:09.926 A:middle
This works really well.

00:36:10.566 --> 00:36:13.866 A:middle
Now, you'll see some dotted

00:36:13.896 --> 00:36:15.626 A:middle
circles on the keyboard.

00:36:15.696 --> 00:36:16.786 A:middle
That's perfectly fine.

00:36:16.886 --> 00:36:18.416 A:middle
They're dependent marks.

00:36:21.906 --> 00:36:24.196 A:middle
And here's the same example in

00:36:24.246 --> 00:36:24.646 A:middle
Arabic.

00:36:25.146 --> 00:36:26.986 A:middle
Again, the same approach is used

00:36:27.046 --> 00:36:28.836 A:middle
all over iOS and macOS, and it

00:36:28.836 --> 00:36:30.496 A:middle
works really well for many

00:36:30.496 --> 00:36:30.966 A:middle
purposes.

00:36:32.336 --> 00:36:34.306 A:middle
And I should also mention that

00:36:34.306 --> 00:36:36.336 A:middle
this is really easy to do with

00:36:36.336 --> 00:36:37.500 A:middle
attributed strings.

00:36:40.596 --> 00:36:43.676 A:middle
Finally, let's go over

00:36:43.676 --> 00:36:44.566 A:middle
everything that we've talked

00:36:44.566 --> 00:36:44.876 A:middle
about.

00:36:48.576 --> 00:36:50.456 A:middle
First off, it's important to

00:36:50.766 --> 00:36:52.356 A:middle
start planning early in your

00:36:52.356 --> 00:36:54.806 A:middle
apps, not only the development,

00:36:54.906 --> 00:36:56.096 A:middle
but also, the design phase.

00:36:59.666 --> 00:37:00.776 A:middle
Once you know the languages

00:36:59.666 --> 00:37:00.776 A:middle
Once you know the languages

00:37:00.776 --> 00:37:02.096 A:middle
you're going to localize into

00:37:02.386 --> 00:37:04.246 A:middle
and plan to extend to in the

00:37:04.246 --> 00:37:06.796 A:middle
future, internationalize as you

00:37:06.796 --> 00:37:07.106 A:middle
go.

00:37:07.816 --> 00:37:09.746 A:middle
Technologies like Auto Layout,

00:37:09.966 --> 00:37:12.626 A:middle
StackViews, and dynamic type are

00:37:12.816 --> 00:37:14.536 A:middle
very simple to adopt while

00:37:14.536 --> 00:37:15.266 A:middle
you're in the process of

00:37:15.266 --> 00:37:16.156 A:middle
building your feature.

00:37:16.586 --> 00:37:17.996 A:middle
But if you finish your project

00:37:17.996 --> 00:37:19.636 A:middle
and try to come back and use

00:37:19.636 --> 00:37:20.426 A:middle
them, then you may have to

00:37:20.426 --> 00:37:21.846 A:middle
completely rearchitect your app.

00:37:21.846 --> 00:37:24.206 A:middle
And that will be a lot of work.

00:37:25.486 --> 00:37:28.056 A:middle
If you're doing something for

00:37:28.056 --> 00:37:29.576 A:middle
which you feel, oh, yeah, there

00:37:29.576 --> 00:37:30.696 A:middle
should be an API for this,

00:37:30.696 --> 00:37:30.916 A:middle
right?

00:37:30.916 --> 00:37:32.916 A:middle
There probably is an API for it.

00:37:33.316 --> 00:37:35.866 A:middle
So, make sure that when you're

00:37:35.916 --> 00:37:37.546 A:middle
doing something like formatting

00:37:37.546 --> 00:37:41.076 A:middle
any kind of data, to make sure

00:37:41.076 --> 00:37:42.096 A:middle
to look to see if there's a

00:37:42.156 --> 00:37:42.906 A:middle
formatter class.

00:37:43.206 --> 00:37:44.276 A:middle
And also, make sure to look to

00:37:44.276 --> 00:37:45.706 A:middle
see if there is an API for

00:37:45.706 --> 00:37:46.776 A:middle
anything you're doing with text

00:37:47.576 --> 00:37:48.656 A:middle
before trying to ruin your own

00:37:48.656 --> 00:37:49.366 A:middle
implementation.

00:37:51.766 --> 00:37:55.266 A:middle
And lastly, ensure that nothing

00:37:55.266 --> 00:37:56.396 A:middle
is lost in translation.

00:37:56.676 --> 00:37:58.766 A:middle
So, the key thing to realize

00:37:58.766 --> 00:38:00.696 A:middle
here is that every localization

00:37:58.766 --> 00:38:00.696 A:middle
here is that every localization

00:38:00.696 --> 00:38:02.266 A:middle
of your app is a unique

00:38:02.266 --> 00:38:02.866 A:middle
experience.

00:38:03.556 --> 00:38:05.456 A:middle
And you need to make sure that

00:38:05.456 --> 00:38:07.626 A:middle
your intent that you specified

00:38:07.686 --> 00:38:08.976 A:middle
in your development language

00:38:09.336 --> 00:38:10.706 A:middle
actually makes it over to all

00:38:10.706 --> 00:38:11.686 A:middle
the other languages that you

00:38:11.726 --> 00:38:12.176 A:middle
support.

00:38:12.176 --> 00:38:14.006 A:middle
And that nothing is lost along

00:38:14.006 --> 00:38:14.296 A:middle
the way.

00:38:15.946 --> 00:38:16.806 A:middle
Thank you, very much.

00:38:17.516 --> 00:38:23.500 A:middle
[ Applause ]
